Pereira then won back to back titles at Porto, but disappointed in Europe, and quit in summer 2013 after missing out on the Everton job. 

He spent a year in Saudi Arabia and was succeeded at Al-Ahli by Christian Gross.

Pereira is currently without a club, meaning he could start immediately, but Palace want time to consider other candidates and have already determined that Keith Millen will be in charge for the matches with Queens Park Rangers and Aston Villa. 

